OL,3,CScientists use lab-grown 'mini guts'
OL,4,Cto study Crohn's disease
OL,6,FResearchers studying Crohn's disease
OL,7,Fhave grown "mini guts" in the lab to
OL,8,Fhelp them further understand the
OL,9,Fcondition.
OL,11,FThe technique has helped the
OL,12,Fscientists discover DNA changes that
OL,13,Fmay play an important role in the
OL,14,Fdisease.
OL,16,FThe mini organs, also called
OL,17,F'organoids', could be used in future
OL,18,Fto help pinpoint more personalised
OL,19,Ftreatments for individual patients.
