OL,3,CScientists use lab-grown 'mini guts'
OL,4,Cto study Crohn's disease
OL,6,Fis a form of inflammatory bowel
OL,7,Fdisease affecting around one in 350
OL,8,Fpeople in the UK. The condition is
OL,9,Flifelong, and one in four of those
OL,10,Faffected will start experiencing
OL,11,Fsymptoms before the age of 18.
OL,13,FSymptoms can have a major impact on
OL,14,Fquality of life and include stomach
OL,15,Fpain, diarrhoea, weight loss and
OL,16,Ffatigue.
OL,18,FTreatment can involve extensive
OL,19,Fsurgery, and exposure to toxic drugs.
