OL,3,CScientists use lab-grown 'mini guts'
OL,4,Cto study Crohn's disease
OL,6,FMatthias Zilbauer, professor of
OL,7,Fpaediatric gastroenterology at the
OL,8,FUniversity of Cambridge and Cambridge
OL,9,FUniversity Hospitals NHS Foundation
OL,10,FTrust (CUH), said: "The number of
OL,11,Fcases of Crohn's disease and IBD are
OL,12,Frising dramatically worldwide,
OL,13,Fparticularly among younger children,
OL,14,Fbut despite decades of research, no
OL,15,Fone knows what causes it."
OL,17,FHe added: "The organoids that we've
OL,18,Fgenerated are primarily from children
OL,19,Fand adolescents.
