OL,3,CScientists use lab-grown 'mini guts'
OL,4,Cto study Crohn's disease
OL,6,FIn a message to other children being
OL,7,Fdiagnosed with the condition, he
OL,8,Fadded: "There are bad days and there
OL,9,Fare good days, but eventually you'll
OL,10,Ffind the right medicine.
OL,12,F"Sometimes it can take a really long
OL,13,Ftime, but eventually they'll find the
OL,14,Fthing that works for you."
OL,16,FIn the future, the findings could help
OL,17,Fpatients such as Arthur access
OL,18,Feffective treatment more quickly.
